suppressPackageStartupMessages({
    library(igraph)
    library(mclust)
    library(gmmase)
})

print("1. Generating a directed, weighted graph...")
## [1] "1. Generating a directed, weighted graph..."
pm <- cbind( c(.2, .001), c(.001, .3) )
g <- sample_sbm(100, pref.matrix=pm, block.sizes=c(30,70), directed=TRUE)
summary(g)
## IGRAPH b86b307 D--- 100 1651 -- Stochastic block-model
## + attr: name (g/c), loops (g/l)
# finding the largest connected component
cl <- igraph::clusters(g)
g <- induced.subgraph(g, which(cl$membership == which.max(cl$csize)))
# add edge weights
E(g)$weight <- runif(ecount(g), 1, 5)
summary(g)
## IGRAPH 00e7b4f D-W- 100 1651 -- Stochastic block-model
## + attr: name (g/c), loops (g/l), weight (e/n)
print("2. Passing-to-rank...")
## [1] "2. Passing-to-rank..."
g <- ptr(g)
summary(g)
## IGRAPH db6d0d0 D-W- 100 1651 -- 
## + attr: weight (e/n)
print("3. Embedding the graph into dmax=20...")
## [1] "3. Embedding the graph into dmax=20..."
dmax <- 20
ase <- embed_adjacency_matrix(g,dmax)

print("4. Finding an elbow (dimension reduction)...")
## [1] "4. Finding an elbow (dimension reduction)..."
elb <- max(getElbows(ase$D)[1],2)

cat("use dhat = ", elb,"\n")
## use dhat =  2
Xhat1 <- ase$X[,1:elb]
Xhat2 <- ase$Y[,1:elb]
Xhat <- cbind(Xhat1,Xhat2)
dim(Xhat)
## [1] 100   4
print("5. Clustering using GMM...")
## [1] "5. Clustering using GMM..."
mc <- Mclust(Xhat)
plot(mc,what="BIC")

summary(mc)
## ----------------------------------------------------
## Gaussian finite mixture model fitted by EM algorithm 
## ----------------------------------------------------
## 
## Mclust VVI (diagonal, varying volume and shape) model with 5 components:
## 
##  log.likelihood   n df      BIC      ICL
##         496.909 100 44 791.1906 777.4614
## 
## Clustering table:
##  1  2  3  4  5 
## 26 15  4 46  9
